{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 2111426, "commentCount": 5726, "commentText": "Maharani Yesubai. 

I am a better writer than a speaker, so here goes. ❤️
I had watched the film called mimi and I loved the film so much that I wanted to invite Laxman sir for the screening of my film goodbye and so i messaged him and that’s when the journey began Cz sir immediately asked me if he could call me and we spoke and he was telling me he wanted to meet me for his next film.. and I thought he was just being nice, but the meeting actually did happen, and it made me so so so happy that it did happen.. I truly thank the universe for this. 

I didn’t know what the story was. I didn’t know why they came to me, I didn’t know how they even saw me as the maharani. I didn’t even know what was happening.. when i actually heard the narration i was confused, shocked but also so grateful, overwhelmed and so so so happy that I didnt know how to react because I didn’t know how we were going to achieve this. 

A girl from the south playing Maharani Yesubai. 
That was something I never had on my radar.. never thought it was possible, and that’s why I love working with people who give us the hope to dream beyond boundaries.

And then the maharani came in all her glory. 
She is fierce - she is powerful - she is graceful - she is a true queen. 
Her love is the love I truly relate to - it’s so pure so divine and so respectful and so true that Maharaj and Maharani are always connected beyond just words.", "viewCount": 0, "location": null, "userTags": ["priyanka.s.borkar", "parthmangla", "vickykaushal09", "tanvichemburkar", "vardannayak", "saibabu2223", "laxman.utekar", "souravv_roy_"]}

post3:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 56478, "commentCount": 611, "commentText": "I am sorry to tell you IT SUCKS B**** but it will get better.🥹❤️‍🩹

Disclaimer: I am not against Tretinoin, I will probably use it again but ONLY under by dermatologist’s guidance and you should too. 

If I was going thought it all over again, this is what I would do. 

1. Go find a dermatologist that feels right for me, i didn’t want to take 10 medications that would screw up my immune system so finding the RIGHT one really matters. Throughout the 6 months my dermatologist didn’t make me do any fancy unnecessary peels or treatments because he was honest with me, that it wouldn’t help. We just did one salicylic acid peel and that’s it. 

2. I would look at my diet and try to eat mostly home cooked food. Here are some of my triggers, whey protein, too much refined sugar and too much processed food. 
3. Stop watching videos on the internet that claim to fix my acne, I am not saying all information is wrong but the magnitude of information is too much and it’s overwhelming. 
4. Mental well being is so important, being around people who don’t make you feel like something is wrong with you is important. But you also need to understand this is not normal and some people will point it out because they do genuinely care. 
5. Be patient, I have no tips for that.🥹

I hope you get through it, I see you and my DMs are open if you want to talk. 

My dermatologist was Mr Siddharth Garekar in Gurgaon. 

[ skincare journey, acne prone skin, chronic acne, tertinoin ]", "viewCount": 1480302, "location": null, "userTags": []}

{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 3258, "commentCount": 49, "commentText": "my new EP ‘finding joy’ 14th Feb 2025 🧩

this is an amalgamation of the three songs I put out last year + 2 new ones! 

I went through a really rough mental journey the last 3 years and I shared the journey with you all and the beautiful thing out that is that I put it into my art- I wrote songs about it!! 

Through the process of being so sad and confused I found myself, myself confidence and my inner ‘joy’ (all the more special as my nickname is joy) 

the visual motif is a 🧩 because at the beginning of last year I had NO intention of putting out music- infact I thought ho Gaya, I’m probably not meant for this but somehow I kept getting pulled into it! So each song sounds different but tells the story finding myself and my joy! Hence it felt right to show a puzzle as I put together myself and my story! 

The two new songs show the happy state of life as through this time, I also fell in love and found joy in growing in a relationship! And intezaar as you know was about that! 

Kahin chale is telling more of that story and its music video also comes out on the 14th! 

The last one Ishaare is my favourite song I’ve EVER written and I have something awesome planned 🧩

But overall this is about finding your own JOY and I know my little version of me would be so proud of me! 

until then :) LOVE YOU and hope you find joy too 💓

Ps our production company and project with @unicefindia also shared the same name! The phase I deemed as the hardest of my life gave me these three beautiful things! @findingjoypictures 💓

post1:
{"mediaType": 1, "likeCount": 108564, "commentCount": 1002, "commentText": "The day I dreamt of long before it was even faintly realistic. When it was still an improbable proposition. Me? On a Vogue cover? With my daughter? Naaa, that’s ludicrous. 

And now, here it is. Or actually here they are. The birth of our daughter, the birth of @indewild, the Vogue cover. 

Together we stand - 7 weeks after giving birth - showcasing the raw and unedited version of ourselves. Purely mother and daughter, eager to take on the challenges of the world, one baby step at a time. 

After two years of blood, sweat, and tears, the power of being different, has come to life. No longer will young women be trapped by societal expectations to cover their insecurities, or feel the need to falsify their persona. Introducing @indewild - a brand like no other. A movement unique to its surroundings. An independent and wild expression of freedom on the day that our “difference becomes our superpower”.

Dedicated to the young girl out there. Consumed by her innocence, mind engrossed with her aspirations to change the world. She is hopeful.
Who is she? Simple. She is a woman. She is a mother. She is you and I. ❤️
——
Huge thanks to the @vogueindia team for making this the mosttt memorable cover shoot of my life. 🙏🏽😩

Styled by Naheed Driver (@naheedee)

{"mediaType": 1, "likeCount": 108564, "commentCount": 1002, "commentText": "The day I dreamt of long before it was even faintly realistic. When it was still an improbable proposition. Me? On a Vogue cover? With my daughter? Naaa, that’s ludicrous.

Together we stand - 7 weeks after giving birth - showcasing the raw and unedited version of ourselves. Purely mother and daughter, eager to take on the challenges of the world, one baby step at a time. 

After two years of blood, sweat, and tears, the power of being different, has come to life. No longer will young women be trapped by societal expectations to cover their insecurities, or feel the need to falsify their persona. Introducing @indewild - a brand like no other. Dedicated to the young girl out there. Consumed by her innocence, mind engrossed with her aspirations to change the world. She is hopeful.

{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 131802, "commentCount": 926, "commentText": "Hello Instagram,

I am not Aakash, I am

Aishwarya’s

post4:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 2109, "commentCount": 33, "commentText": "What I think about this lube-as-primer trend. I get why it seems like a good idea, it’s smooth, lightweight, and made for sensitive areas. But here’s the thing…

Our vaginal pH is acidic, and lube is designed for that environment, not your face. When you use it as a primer, the pH mismatch + preservatives not meant for facial skin can disrupt your microbiome, cause irritation, breakouts, or even fungal acne. 🦠

And while water-based lubes seem like a safer bet, they often contain humectants, thickeners, and preservatives that might feel hydrating but can also be sticky, clog pores, or throw off your skin balance.

So while it’s a fun hack, it’s not the best option for long-term skin health or makeup performance. A good primer will actually help with oil control, longevity, and keep your skin barrier happy!

#certifiedskincareconsultant #cosmeticformulatorintraining #skincare", "viewCount": 254472, "location": null, "userTags": []}

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 1893, "commentCount": 111, "commentText": "SAVE or SPLURGE?

Not all hair products need to break the bank… but some? absolutely worth the investment. here’s why…

SAVE on shampoos & conditioners
cleansers are rinse-off products… their job is to remove dirt, oil, and product buildup, not to penetrate the hair shaft. as long as a shampoo effectively cleanses without stripping and a conditioner smooths the cuticle, drugstore options work just fine. sulfates? silicones? totally fine if formulated well.

SPLURGE on treatments (not everyone needs these)
bond builders like K18 or Olaplex work at a molecular level to repair broken disulfide bonds, something a basic conditioner can’t do. Scalp serums with peptides and caffeine support follicle health over time.

SAVE on oils & basic moisturizers
most hair oils are just a blend of silicones and lightweight oils that coat the hair for shine… a budget-friendly serum can do the same.

The takeaway? invest in the treatments that actually change your hair’s health long term specially if you have damaged hair from bleach/heat or are losing/greying hair… and save your cash on the basics. haircare should be strategic, not just expensive.", "viewCount": 193814, "location": null, "userTags": []}

post10:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 2683, "commentCount": 42, "commentText": "Eye creams and serums with wand applicators are designed to be safe for use around the eyes

Large brands like  L'oreal, Estee lauder, Unilever, P&G don't just throw products on the market… their formulas have to go through rigorous testing, especially for sensitive areas like the eyes… their packaging and applicators are tested for hygiene and stability, and their preservation systems ensure safety with regular use

if an applicator wasn’t safe, the brand legally couldn’t market it for the eye area… companies work with toxicologists and regulatory experts to make sure these products meet strict global safety standards

of course, proper use matters… always follow the directions on the label, keep applicators clean, and avoid direct contact with the eye itself… but the idea that using a built-in applicator is automatically bad is just misinformation. these products are designed with both efficacy and hygiene in mind

#cosmeticformulatorintraining #certifiedskincareconsultant", "viewCount": 354195, "location": null, "userTags": ["lorealparis", "unilever", "esteelaudercompanies", "esteelauderin", "lorealparis.india", "hul.news"]}

post12:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 1919, "commentCount": 64, "commentText": "People think expensive shampoos work better just because they cost more… but here’s the truthbrands price their products based on marketing, target audience, and perceived value, not because the formulas are radically different.

Most shampoos, whether ₹200 or ₹2000, have the same core ingredients:
✔ Surfactants to cleanse
✔ Conditioning agents to soften
✔ Preservatives to keep it stable

So why the price gap? Because different consumers want different thingssome people prefer luxury packaging, exclusivity, and a sensory experience, while others just want something that works without the markup.

Neither is wrong, but just know that PRICE ≠ PERFORMANCE when it comes to shampoo and conditioners… spend where it actually makes a difference!", "viewCount": 280331, "location": null, "userTags": []}

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 293918, "commentCount": 2264, "commentText": "Dear soul reading this, 
According to numerology, 2024 has been a year governed by Saturn. 

Saturn tests two aspects of your existence : 
1. Your ability to work hard through storms.
2. Your ability to stay humble through glory.

Saturn is a task master. Saturn is an examiner.

It's not been an easy year for me either. I have put my head down and worked through it all.

Some times, while my head was down and working... my eyes teared up with the pressure of being an adult. 

Some times while my head was down and working... God gave me moments to smile & breathe.

It's been a year that's tested me to my last degree of resistance.

It's a year that's taught me : Faith and belief can overcome the false storms of what we call "suffering"

My knee injury was a gift as much as my national award was.

My poor mental health was a gift as much as public adulation was.

Life's purpose is to grow. Often through the dungeons of suffering as much as through the dungeons of success.

Get even healthier this year.
Meditate deeply this year.
Pursue peace this year.

But whatever you do, believe that God is with you through every step.

Happy 2025, have a blessed one!

2025 - Year of "Mars"

Pour your intensity into the speed and strength of your work.
Now overcome your own demons.
Now grow more easily. 

#spirituality #theranveershow #God", "viewCount": 6171589, "location": null, "userTags": []}
post12:
{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 420230, "commentCount": 2307, "commentText": "Merry Christmas to you all, from Goa. It's been the most eventful Christmas of my life. 

Gonna be very vulnerable in this write up.

We're perfectly fine & well now. But yesterday at 6:00 pm or so, my girlfriend and I had to be rescued from a bit of a situation.

We both love swimming in the open ocean. I've been doing this since I was a kid. 

But yesterday we got swept away by an underwater current. 
This has happened to me before but I've never been alongside a companion.

It's easy to swim out of one alone. It's very hard to pull someone out with you.

After a 5-10 minute struggle, we called for help and were promptly rescued by a family of 5 swimming nearby.

We're both good swimmers but the fury of nature is such that it WILL test your limits at some point.

A casual, fun dip in the waves was interrupted by an underwater current that toppled both of us. The next thing we knew was that we were both struggling to stay afloat.

There was a point during the ordeal where I swallowed a lot of water and started fading away a little bit. That's when I decided to shout for help.

Deep gratitude to the family of the IPS officer husband and IRS officer wife who saved us both.

This experience left us feeling both blank as well as grateful. We felt the protection of God throughout the incident.

As we moved into today's Christmas, we're simply full of gratitude for being alive.

Almost feel like this one life experience has changed my perspective towards living.

Writing this because I've always shared these moments with you all. Full of emotion and gratitude today. A deep thank you and big hugs to each one of you reading this!

Last evening, I decided to call my brother @brother.salvador to convey the Christmas Eve incident. He performed a prayer for us where we thanked Lord Jesus Christ as well as the God above us. 

This has been a very very memorable Goa holiday for me. From discovering secret Murtis at @aliladiwagoa to touching the life-death barrier.

I guess 2025 is going to be more blessed than ever.

{"mediaType": 1, "likeCount": 37975, "commentCount": 67, "commentText": ""When it comes to the content that OTT platforms offer, I think initially people were just shooting in the dark, as no-one knew what would and wouldn’t work. But eventually, everyone realised the freedom that OTT offers, in terms of the stories we could shed light on. The best part was that you didn’t need the big names in order for the shows to do well...it’s more content driven," shares actor Aisha Ahmed (@aisharahmed).
⠀
"Being an actor, validation is definitely important. But my role in Minus One [2019] made me look deep inside to realise that I should not limit myself. I am looking forward to exploring different genres—I want to do everything because being an actor brings me a lot of joy. My acting coach...well, actually, someone who conducted acting workshops for Minus One, told me: ‘You have to serve the art, not the artist’. Which means you don’t think that you are bigger than the work that you are doing. You must let go of who you are as a person, your reservations and ideologies, and just serve what you are on set to serve," she adds.

post1:
{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 398301, "commentCount": 1492, "commentText": "6000 People for Hindi comedy in the middle of New York Manhatan at @thetheateratmsg ✅

Thank you @vidya_mdesai @instafunny_manan @rajivnemaindori @kaneezsurka @zeeshan_malang for being by my side while I loose my mind on such a big day. 

Also thanks to my team @rishabhnahar @xankurkaushikx @manuvijayan27 @gauravvaz the team from UTA and OutBack 

I am still processing… thode din baat theek se bataunga kaisa laga. Abhi ke liye samjh lo ki it was a big day not just because of the Venue or capacity but some of my fav people were in the audience that day. 

Like @alisethiofficial one of the greatest musician of our generation. 

@vikaskhannagroup bhai who is opening the best restaurants in the world called @bungalowny in New York. 

@kalpenn bhai he left his rehearsal just to support me. 

Anjaan desh, paraye logon ke beech itna pyar karne wale log mil gaye aur kya hi chahiye. Log bahut door-door se drive kar ke aaye they, bahut se log toh 2-3 ghante ki flight se bhi aaye they. Mai yeh sab kabhi bhool nahi paunga. 

It was big for me, for comedy in India and for our desi culture here. ❤️

Thank you @marcusrussellprice for the pictures bro

Thank you @zeebamiraie for all the cool outfits for the tour!!?", "viewCount": 0, "location": {"name": "Madison Square Garden", "address": "4 Pennsylvania Plaza", "city": "New York, New York", "has_viewer_saved": false, "pk": 2082352, "short_name": "Madison Square Garden", "facebook_places_id": 28859306498, "external_source": "facebook_places", "lng": -73.992893513651, "lat": 40.750513547361}, "userTags": ["kaneezsurka", "rajivnemaindori", "vidya_mdesai", "xankurkaushikx", "instafunny_manan", "zeeshan_malang", "vikaskhannagroup", "alisethiofficial", "thetheateratmsg"]}

post3:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 228866, "commentCount": 1313, "commentText": "My US visa was first rejected in June, 2011. Why? Because I was unmarried or jobless, I guess. My dream was to travel to LA with the last batch of my savings to try my luck at the food network to pursue my dream of being a chef in the food content industry! I wanted to merge my passion for cooking and acting, together. I was shattered when this last attempt to live my dream was rejected (after having already faced multiple rejections in Mumbai in 2010).

After a month out of nowhere I got a call from 'FoodFood' tv channel to come for a life changing audition, later I was told it was through an email I had dropped back in the year 2010 when I was struggling to be in Mumbai. After my audition I was shortlisted to be on Mahachallenge. Life took a turn on that show, I went on to win it and I also met my idol Chef Sanjeev Kapoor.

Then 9 months later - March, 2012 - I was invited to the US to represent Indian cuisine and a young interviewer at the Visa consulate asked "Why was your Visa rejected, I can't understand, also with a polite smile he told me that I didn't have to carry amy newspaper clippings to prove a point. Please teach me more about Indian food" he said. I wish I could explain to him that life had happened to me. If I had gone earlier to the US, who knows I might have struggled all my life. My rejection made me who I am today. This is Arbhi tuk canape that I made for a demo in New York to showcase how beautiful Indian cuisine is. I would not change a single thing about this journey because if you dare to dream, life will happen to you.
.
.
Sindhi Arbi Tuk Canape 

Boil 250g Arbi 
for 10 minutes 

Strain & set aside 

Fry them for 10 mins in low medium hot oil

Look at that 
Cool them down 
& smash them 
Fry in super hot oil 
Till GBC 

Tuk Masala
1tbsp Chili powder
1 tbsp Coriander powder
1/4tsp Haldi powder 
1/2tbsp Jeera powder 
1.5 tbsp Aamchur powder 
Salt to taste

Toss tuk and masala together 

Slice 1 onion 
1 inch Ginger, julienne 
Lemon juice to taste 
Kala namak to taste 
Mix well 

Grate 1 Cucumber 
Squeeze out the excess water 

200g Thick yogurt 
Add the cucumber 
2 Garlic cloves, grated
Coriander and Mint 
Salt, mix well.

Assemble!", "viewCount": 11501474, "location": null, "userTags": []}

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 21394, "commentCount": 257, "commentText": "Best meal to start my birthday week! Gujarati Patra with Hara Lehsun Khichdi, Patra Stem Raita and Shalgam Gobhi Gajar pickle. This meal was totally worth the effort. Soul is extra satisfied. Many people make different versions of patra also known as patrode or alu wadi. 
.
.
Gujarati Patra with Hara lasun khichadi 
.
For the Patra
.
Cut & clean colocasia leaves, as shown 
Roll them out lightly 
to make them pliable 
Wash & dry them too 
20g Imli 
40g Jaggery 
1/2 cup Hot water 
Let everything soak & melt well 
2 cups Besan 
30g Rice flour 
2 1/2 tbsp Ginger garlic chili paste 
1/2 tsp Baking soda 
1/2 tsp Ajwain 
1 tbsp Coriander powder 
1/2 tbsp Red chili powder 
1/2 tsp Bhuna jeera powder 
1/2 tsp Haldi powder 
1/2 tsp Garam masala powder 
Salt to taste 
Strain the imli jaggery mix 
1/2 cup Water 
Mix well 
Layer each leaf with the besan batter 
& roll as shown 
Steam the patra for 20 mins 
or till a skewer inserted comes out clean! 
Once done 
cut as shown 
2 tbsp Oil 
1/2 tsp Jeera 
1/2 tsp Mustard seeds 
1 tsp Sesame seeds 
A few curry leaves 
Add the sliced patra 
& pan sear from both sides 
till GBC 🔥🤤
Garnish with freshly chopped coriander 
& serve hot
.
For the Patra Raita (Thank you @keertidacooks for the inspo)
.
Clean & cut the colocasia stems, as shown Roll
1 tsp Ghee 
A few curry leaves

Add the stems 
& sauté well

Add the sautéed stems 
& mix well
. 
For the Hare lasun ki khichadi 
.
1/4 cup Moong dal 
1/4 cup Toor dal

1 Black cardamom 
1/2 tsp Jeera

Salt to taste 
Water, as required

Pressure cook for 3 whistles 
For the tadka of the khichadi 
.

1/4 tsp Hing 
1 tsp Mustard seeds 
1 Green chili, chopped 
A handful of Green garlic, chopped 
A few curry leaves 
Add the tadka to the khichadi

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 44881, "commentCount": 256, "commentText": "Have you ever tried this? A green garlic and spring onion Juar Jo Dodo! A Sindhi winter special bread that's shaped with your fingers on a tawa and usually served with tidali dal or dahi. My friend Chetna was here in Mumbai from UK and we wanted her to experience winters at their best! The Orange Raita was inspired by the Pahadi Chakotre ka saan which is basically like a pomelo salad or raita. Trust me when I say this, this raita is finger licking good! Also shaping that roti is easier than it looks, just be mindful of the tawa and you can keep it on low to medium heat. 
.
.
Jowar Jo Dodo aur Santre ka Raita 
.
For the Jowar Dodo
.
Trim & cut Green garlic 
Chop some Spring onions 
2 cups Jowar atta 
1 Green chili, chopped 
3tbsp Spring onion greens, chopped 
3 tbsp Fresh coriander, chopped 
3tbsp Green garlic, chopped 
1 tsp Bhuna Jeera powder 
1 tsp Red chili powder
Salt to taste 
Mix everything well 
Add water little by little to form a semi soft dough 
Cover & rest dough for 15 mins
Carefully flatten the dough on a hot tawa 
Sprinkle some water 
Cover & cook for 2 to 3 minutes 
Add some ghee 
Baste it well 
Flip & cook from both sides till 
Golden brown & crispy 🤤🔥
.
For the Santre ka Raita 
.
Biryani 🤨?
Pulao 🤨? 
.
Dry some mint in the microwave 
& make it into a powder 😎
De-skin & de-seed 🍊 
Remove the flesh 
1 cup Whisked yogurt 
Add the oranges 
1 tsp Garlic granules 
1/2 tsp Bhuna jeera powder 
1/2 tbsp Jaggery 
Salt to taste 
Black salt to taste 
Mix well 
1 tbsp Pudina powder 
1 Green chili, chopped 
Mix well 
🤌🏻🤤
Serve with Jowar Dodo 
Delishaaas 🤤🔥", "viewCount": 1913901, "location": null, "userTags": ["chetnamakan"]}

post11:
{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 1076693, "commentCount": 1164, "commentText": "My first venture into the world of sports — pickleball, of all things — has been so transformative! I came into it with a lifetime of hesitation, ‘cos I had always avoided sports because I hate losing. 🙂

But something about the qualities of athletes and the spirit of sportsmanship have always intrigued me. So when the opportunity came to own the @chennaisuperchamps, I dove right in. 

And I’m SO glad I did. 

The excitement, the growth, the realisation that in sports it’s all about learning, evolving beyond wins and losses, and pushing beyond limits... has taught me so much.

Our team gave everything, showing relentless spirit, especially with challenges stacked against us and our top player not being able to join us. Their grit and resilience has given me a fresh perspective. 

And I couldn’t have asked for better teammates than Raj and Himank on this rollercoaster journey. 
This is just the beginning!! 💪🏼💪🏼💪🏼

Truly amazed at how well the league was put together. It was spectacular! Kudos @worldpickleballofficial @gaurav.natekar @aratiponnappa", "viewCount": 0, "location": null, "userTags": ["karnrateria", "sj.lim__", "thaddea23", "acp_pb", "tyratjc", "perez_edward", "mayank_sn", "pickleballlover", "joeyfariaspickleball", "eblasz_pickleball", "tanner.pickleball", "mandoa_media", "worldpickleballofficial", "chennaisuperchamps"]}

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 73, "commentCount": 7, "commentText": "Serengeti was SO magnificent and it really made me feel small in the best possible way🦏🦒🦓🐆

The unbothered elephant outside my tent was a reminder that I’m just a guest. 

When questioned about the fenceless campsite, I was humbled by the guide who said “why would there by a fence? This place belongs to the animals, not us”

The piercing gaze of the leopard had chills running down my spine. 

As I witnessed thousands of wilderbeasts migrating, the ground beneath me trembled. 

The baby giraffe fearing hungry predators reminded me of how my own worries feel so silly sometimes. 

The world is vast, wild and beautifully indifferent to my day to day problems, and somehow that realization is liberating and makes me want to travel more🪄

28 countries done! Where should I go next?🙇🏼‍♀️

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 27, "commentCount": 0, "commentText": "Seas of Serenity | SCUBA & Yoga Retreat in the Andaman Islands 🌊 

Why are we practicing yoga alongside SCUBA diving on this retreat? 

Having practiced both, I strongly feel yogāsana and scuba diving meet and overlap on some aspects beautifully - as introspective journeys, they instill lightness, calmness and awe within us. Scuba diving requires mental clarity, controlled breathing, and physical endurance, all of which are nurtured through yoga.

The twice-daily yogasana practices are designed specifically to complement scuba diving by:

	•	Preparing the Body: Gentle movement helps improve flexibility, mobility in the hips, stability in the back and spine and balance, which are essential for navigating underwater environments and handling scuba gear with ease. 🙅‍♀️

	•	Enhancing Breathing: Pranayama (breathing techniques) trains you to control and deepen your breath, a skill crucial for conserving air, maintaining neutral buoyancy and staying calm underwater. 😮‍💨

	•	Understanding Physiology: Yoga improves awareness of your body’s systems, enabling you to respond intuitively to the sensations and changes occurring within the body during diving. 🫁

	•	Energizing and Grounding: The practices will leave you both invigorated and centered, helping you embrace the underwater experience with calm focus and readiness. 🍃

By integrating yoga and scuba diving, you’ll cultivate a deeper connection to your physical and mental self, enabling you to dive not just into the ocean, but into a heightened state of awareness and presence. 🤿🧘‍♀️
.
.
.
.
.
Join us from the 7th - 14th of March, 2025 
This retreat is perfect for you if you are looking to get your first certification as a recreational SCUBA diver ☀️

{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 175, "commentCount": 9, "commentText": "This was a space where we didn’t need the permission to interrupt and ask questions, break into spiralling debates or unapologetically disagree. Because such is a healthy, sturdy yet cushioned relationship between a teacher and their students; such is a place of sustainable growth. 

The four walls within which the past is brought back to life, historical milestones are recollected with wonderment, a unanimous hope emerges for a promising future and most importantly, each present curiosity is given space. Within these walls exists no hierarch - what exists is different minds that are eager inquire with sincerity. 

I experienced such an environment for 5 days in mysore where I wouldn’t say time stood still, rather time, for once, didn’t interfere. The morning’s questions poured themselves into our midday coffees, which brought us to life during our afternoon lectures. These didn’t remain lectures for long because each our unique experiences taught us all something new. This dialogue grew voluminous and took a spot on our dinner plates and our reflections from the day were like a sweet lullaby to finally put us to sleep at night. And then on repeat. 

I am not yet equipped to write about what I theoretically learned and that, which I am pondering over can’t be put into words. I know that I wear the warmth of each one of you and my vulnerability has gained a new vigour. 

Large amounts of gratitude, respect and a gigantic hug for my dearest @yogaprasad_institute and @rcp_inflow ✨💙🙏 

The wise, magical and incredibly humble beings I spent these 5 days with - all my love to each of you ♥️", "viewCount": 0, "location": {"name": "Kurma Shala", "address": "", "city": "Mysore, Karnataka", "has_viewer_saved": false, "pk": 103575791797988, "short_name": "Kurma Shala", "facebook_places_id": 103575791797988, "external_source": "facebook_places", "lng": 76.629095710411, "lat": 12.332149645246}, "userTags": ["nush_y", "vandana_taamararasa", "sushiyogi", "yogaprasad_institute", "nicoleanthony.yoga", "shivi.yoga", "yogi.santa", "rcp_inflow", "beingmeraklis", "nuyoga03", "gow.withtheflow", "ayam_extensions"]}

{"mediaType": 1, "likeCount": 164, "commentCount": 17, "commentText": "We are doing everything in our power to run away from or push away even the slightest sensation of pain. Either we keep it under wraps out of guilt and shame or we latch onto someone’s advice out of helplessness or we turn bitter just wondering what we did to deserve this pain.. 

When this pain is somehow alleviated, how many of us truly ponder over the joy we are experiencing? How many of us have an ongoing dialogue with parts of our body when they are “performing their job” well or parts of our mind that are trying to perceive the world around us with sparks of hope? 

Most things I write are sprouting curiosities that tickle me by me - and as much as I enjoy resonating with people around me, I write with the hope of resonating with myself. 

I found myself partaking in an interesting conversation the other day - ‘what does it mean to warm up before getting into a situation that demands alignment and depth?’ - asana practice would be a relatable example. 
Does it mean I do some repeated movements to get my heart rate going or does it mean I reach out to specific parts of my body to speak to them separately and prepare them? 

Maybe this conversation could just be me telling them they’re doing a good job and I have no intention of hurting them, maybe this little check-in would ease their nervousness or me sending my breath to them would warm them up. 

What if similarly, I could caress parts of my life with gentleness and not look for the creases, rather slide my touch across ironed out soft textures? 

Do I have the vocabulary for that conversation? 
And if I realise don’t - it’s never too late to learn a new language :) 

📸 - revealing the magic of @mister.bora bit by bit 🌸
.
.
.
.
.
.

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 10, "commentCount": 0, "commentText": "One of the most important concepts in trading, without which it is impossible to trade effectively, is the time frame. 

A time frame represents a period of price movement. If the time frame is one day, a new candle or bar will appear with each new trading day.

The higher the time frame selected, the more accurate the signals and the lower the risks. Conversely, the lower the time frame chosen, the less accurate the signals and the higher the risks. 

By analyzing lower time frames, we assess the short-term price behavior of an asset; medium-term time frames help us understand the medium-term trend; and higher time frames reveal the long-term trend.

There is no ‘best’ time frame for trading, just as there is no ‘best’ strategy for trading. The choice of a time frame depends solely on the trader’s subjective preferences and objectives. However, for beginners, starting with the weekly time frame is a great way to begin, as it provides a clearer view of the market with less ‘noise’.

AKELA 🙈🙈🙈 
 joh tum aur mai hoon 😂 haha, I’m so funny like that 🤣! 
But broooo, lemme tell you, this has to be the best cake I’ve everrr had 🎂! NGL, when I speak about the softness of the #cake 🍰, it was AMAZING 😍!

The fact that it was banana 🍌 didn’t sit right with me at first 🤔, since I’ve never been a big fan of #banana smoothies 🍹 or anything banana-related anyyythingg  But this cake was a game-changer !

post9:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 479501, "commentCount": 18831, "commentText": "Gajar mera pasandida fal hai 🥕
Kya apako pata nahi yeh kitna istemaal me aata hai? 🤔🥰 We cannot be friends if you don’t like #carrots in general 🤭! I honestly think it’s such a good food or whatever you call it 🤷‍♀️. I call it a fruit because it is a #fruit 🍉! lol.

I don’t understand how people who live outside have never tasted Gaja ka Halwa 🍰. It’s the most poorest thing you can have in the winters ❄️. I’ve always been a fan of a good carrot juice 🥤. Since I was a kid 👧. I liked a sweet freshly squeezed orange or carrot juice, maybe even sometimes a pomegranate juice if I was privileged enough 😏.

Carrots are good for your eyes 👀, and I never believe them because I got glasses anyway 🤓, and they would force me to drink carrot #juice, but it honestly didn’t do anything good to my eyes, so I think the technically lied to me 😂. My whole life, damn! Now that I think of your parents and their scams when we were kids 🤣... are so true!

I think there should be like something legal for that as well 🚔 because I never got the money that my relatives gave my mom to keep for me 🤑. I think I must be a millionaire 💸 if I got that kind of money! Anyway, back to the carrot juice #review, my #honestfeedback would definitely be a positive one gosh i love doing some #snackreview always so def a #recommended from my end🥕.

I always think it’s such an honour to just eat a carrot with normal dinner 🍴 because who doesn’t like carrots? 🤷‍♀️ I think I have way too much to say about carrots now 🤣, and that’s all. I feel like a second-grade student writing an essay about carrots 📝!

I’ll end this by saying drop a 🥕🥕 if you think that size is big :p (not gonna say which). Love you so much! ❤️", "viewCount": 29395872, "location": null, "userTags": []}

S.M.S thakur vidyalaya from Ulhasnagar has kids who work in mills and cut clothes to support their families. But what came as a surprise is how unaware they are about their own bodies.

These girls needed knowledge, awareness and basic understanding of what nature and biology has brought to them. So I thought, let the boys take the lead and understand MENSTRUAL EDUCATION thoroughly. 

They had an extensive workshop, which was led by our expert @asmitajadhav_98 

And they taught and imparted the knowledge to the girls as they learnt.

I was in the awe of this day and conversations that were never done in this entire village.

Real change begins when we talk about things that need to be talked about. And of course, the revolution is right in front of your eyes.✨

Outfit: @esthreall 💖
Thanks to @nuawoman for sending our girls some amazing menstrual products :)
All hearts to @daybreakpass for empowering and helping us with the best products✨", "viewCount": 11781545, "location": null, "userTags": []}

post10:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 30666, "commentCount": 193, "commentText": "“No one ever told me about 𝗽𝗲𝗿𝗶𝗼𝗱𝘀. I grew up in an orthodox family. Dad sold fruits & vegetables & Maa was a BMC officer. Childhood was tough; we were struggling. Back then, putting food on the table was a bigger priority than educating your child on topics like mental health & menstruation.

But at 𝟭𝟯, I began noticing things–once when we were invited to a Puja, Maa said, ‘𝗜 𝘄𝗼𝗻’𝘁 𝗯𝗲 𝗮𝗯𝗹𝗲 𝘁𝗼 𝗴𝗼.’ She wouldn’t set foot inside a temple on ‘those days’ & neither would she sleep in the same bedroom as Papa. Then when I entered my late teens, that’s when I 1st came to know about it–one day, I noticed Maa visiting the washroom constantly. I asked, ‘Are you okay?’ She didn’t say anything but Bhai said, ‘Maa is on her period.’ I didn’t even know what that was! Around the same time the girl I was dating told me she was ‘bleeding’ from inside. That’s how at 20, I started educating myself.

That led to a lot of questions like ’Why aren’t women allowed to enter the temple?’ I even asked Maa. She said, ‘I’ve been raised that way.’ I then spoke to my sister-in-law, friends, & my girlfriend!
I wanted to create a change–so last year, I distributed pads to women who had never used them before. Then a few months back, a friend said, ‘I have such bad mood swings due to my periods.’ I wanted to make her feel happy. So while I ordered food for her, I decided to do something sweet for other girls too…
I decided to go to marine drive to 𝗰𝗲𝗹𝗲𝗯𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗲 those women who were on their period. I know I couldn’t reduce their pain but for a few minutes, I could help them forget about it. I wrote messages on a card, gave them flowers, chocolates, & a big hug! A lot of people might find this ‘cringe.’ But those girls’, ‘Your sweet gesture made my pain bearable,’ made me feel I had done something right.

People need to know this is normal. We need to start a conversation–where men know this is 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗮 𝘁𝗮𝗯𝗼𝗼; where women don’t find it uncomfortable talking about their periods. And I am trying to do exactly that. I grew up in a household where even saying ‘periods’ made people uncomfortable. So, today, I’m making sure I’m doing my bit to normalize it!”", "viewCount": 1040944, "location": {"name": "Mumbai - मुंबई", "address": "Mumbai", "city": "Mumbai, Maharashtra", "has_viewer_saved": false, "pk": 558866570980556, "short_name": "Mumbai - मुंबई", "facebook_places_id": 558866570980556, "external_source": "facebook_places", "lng": 72.832340567712, "lat": 18.952895746821}, "userTags": ["sidiously_"]}

post1:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 1758, "commentCount": 24, "commentText": "Share with me your travel dream? Aise kya sapne aur shauk hai tumhare 🔥i really want to know 

I used to dream of riding horses, now where ever I see one my first response is can I ride one? 

For 30 years, life was all about work and responsibility. But then I started traveling, and something changed. The urge to learn, to experience, to see if I could.

In Kazakhstan, I rented horses whenever I could. In Mongolia, I rode for days through endless landscapes. In Kyrgyzstan, I hiked on horseback. And with every ride, I felt something no expensive car could ever give—freedom.

This is just the beginning. More horses, more countries, more adventure 🥹

.
.
.
.
#contentcreator #cinematic #travelmore", "viewCount": 24553, "location": null, "userTags": []}
post2:
{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 4376, "commentCount": 60, "commentText": "When you’re 60 and your knees don’t support you🥹, what stories will you tell?

“That I was a good employee?” Hell no.

Tell me about the time you got lost in a random country with no phone signal. Or when you swam with sharks (or at least thought you did). About that hostel night where strangers turned into lifelong friends. The sketchy taxi ride that almost made you question your life choices.

Life’s too short to play it safe. Book that flight. Talk to the weird stranger. Say yes to the unknown. Because in the end, no one remembers the meetings they attended—they remember the stories they lived.
.
.
.
.

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 1195, "commentCount": 37, "commentText": "What does a road trip mean to you? 🚗💨

Is it the open road? The unplanned stops? The deep talks at 2 AM? Or just blasting cringe yet legendary songs with your friends? 🎶😂

For me, a road trip is all of it. It’s wearing anything, being anything, playing bad Himesh Reshammiya songs, sometimes Honey Singh, sometimes Khaabon Ke Parinday from ZNMD.

And of course, there’s always that one friend who never wakes up and another who never stops talking—but never makes sense. 🤡

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 3066, "commentCount": 60, "commentText": "Is this the most beautiful place in India?

How untouched and pristine is the Anini valley in Arunachal Pradesh 🥹 and i have no regret saying - its now my favourite valley ⛰️

The locals worship nature here, and for them, nature is everything. Hence, there are many beautiful waterfalls in this valley and lakes. 

📍How to visit Anini valley?
- You can start your journey from Dibrugarh in Assam and then head to Roing in Arunachal. Keep 3 days in hand to explore this valley. The roads are bad, but it’s totally worth it. 
Sadly, public transport is scarce, but you can self-drive or go in a group trip.
.
.
.
.

post5:
{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 2837, "commentCount": 46, "commentText": "Would you take on a trip like this?

Mongolia is the BAAAP of all road trips 💯If you’ve been to Ladakh or Spiti, your next ride should be here. Endless open roads, no phone network, just you and the wild.

I traveled with 5 strangers from Japan, Singapore, Canada, and the US. 15 days of camping on the road, fighting crazy winds, fixing car breakdowns, dealing with theft, and even going without food for days. 
But that’s what makes road trips real—the adventure, the struggle, the freedom.

💰 Budget Breakdown (Yes, it’s that cheap!)
* Daily Meals: $8-10 (but options are limited in remote areas)
* Homestay: $8-10 per night (for two people)
* E-Visa: Super easy and costs just $5 → www.evisa.mn
* Car & Fuel: Biggest expense—expect to cover 800km per day
✈️ Travel Tips (For my Indian fam!)
* No direct flights? No problem! Route hack: Hong Kong → Kazakhstan → Ulaanbaatar
* Car Rentals: $45-60/day (split with your squad for a budget-friendly trip)
* Camping: The best way to experience Mongolia—sleep under galaxies", "viewCount": 47408, "location": null, "userTags": []}
post6:
{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 2304, "commentCount": 47, "commentText": "What suggestions would ‘YOU’ ☝️give to your younger self? (it would help all of us surely)

But if I could sit down with 21-year-old Sayan, I’d tell him—

Life will get messy before it makes sense. It will get better before it gets worse. You’ll love the wrong people, lose yourself, and even go through a divorce. But one day, you’ll be loved in a way that makes you feel worthy.

You’ll leave that cubicle job you hated and find a passion that pays you. The same dreams people laughed at—the filmmaker, the traveler—you’ll live them. The same teeth gap, the same voice, the same skin they mocked, will be part of the story that sets you apart.

It takes time. But you’ll make it. So be brave. And never let anyone tell you otherwise.

.
.
.
#contentcreator #travelling #explorepage #selftransformation #filmaker", "viewCount": 0, "location": null, "userTags": []}

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 167011, "commentCount": 201, "commentText": "Spent 10 hours at Changi Airport 💯 before my flight to Delhi, and it felt like an entire city inside an airport! 

From rooftop pools to free movie theaters, budget-friendly food, and insane activities—this place has it all. 
Plus, multiple 7-Elevens mean you don’t have to splurge on airport prices!

Jewel Changi Airport:

✨ HSBC Rain Vortex – The world’s tallest indoor waterfall
✨ Hedge Maze & Mirror Maze – Fun challenges to get lost in
✨ Manulife Sky Nets – Walk, jump, or bounce on suspended nets
✨ Canopy Park – Gardens, foggy bowls & interactive attractions

Terminal 1:

✨ Rooftop Pool & Jacuzzi – Swim while watching planes take off
✨ Cactus Garden – A chill spot with unique desert plants

Terminal 2:

✨ Enchanted Garden – Motion-activated lights & greenery
✨ Orchid Garden – A peaceful koi pond surrounded by orchids

Terminal 3:

✨ Butterfly Garden – A tropical space with 1,000+ butterflies
✨ The Slide@T3 – The world’s tallest airport slide (12m high!)
✨ Crystal Garden – Hand-blown glass sculptures in a stunning display

Terminal 4:

✨ Petalclouds – A mesmerizing kinetic art installation
✨ Peranakan Gallery – Showcasing Singapore’s rich cultural heritage

Changi Airport makes layovers feel like an adventure! Would you explore an airport like this? 

#ChangiAirport #singaporediaries #contentcreator #travelmore #adventure", "viewCount": 3831688, "location": null, "userTags": []}

{"mediaType": 2, "likeCount": 4317, "commentCount": 60, "commentText": "Doggo and Pahad 🥹❤️

post11:
{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 9658, "commentCount": 191, "commentText": "Life always gives you two roads. One will take you to your dreams, the other to regret. 
And most of the time, the right road? It’s the harder one. Hai na? 🙈

The one where you doubt yourself. Where it gets lonely. Where you fail over and over again. Where you feel like giving up.

I know because I’ve lived it.

Till 30, I was just failing—
Failed in school 🥹
Failed in college 🥹
Failed at work 🥹
Failed in relationships 🥹
Failed in marriage 🥹
Failed as a son, a husband, an entrepreneur 🥹

I’ve lost count of how many times life knocked me down. But I never lost hope. Because somewhere, on some random YouTube video, I heard something that stuck with me—being in discomfort means you’re growing.

So I told myself: one more day, one more challenge.

And the results: the @sayannath you follow now 🙈

Not because I had it easy. Not because I was lucky. But because I chose the hard road—and I kept walking.

Dosto! Just keep walking 👣  I love you all 

.
.
.
.
#contentcreator #lifelessons #exploremore", "viewCount": 0, "location": null, "userTags": []}
post12:
{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 4503, "commentCount": 64, "commentText": "Fear doesn’t mean you can’t do it 🔥 it just means you’re human. The real magic happens when you push forward anyway, turning fear into fuel instead of a barrier.

I’ve always been someone who let fear hold me back—fear of judgment, fear of failure, fear of the unknown. Because of it, I missed out on so many things—learning the guitar, pushing through engineering, asking for a raise in my job, taking creative risks on Instagram 🥲

So ask yourself: what’s the worst that could happen? And more importantly, what’s the best? More often than not, the best outcome outweighs the fear. Keep going—you’ve got this.

I love you ❤️ all 

.
.
.
.
#contentcreator #travelgram #travelmore #lifestyle", "viewCount": 0, "location": null, "userTags": []}

{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 27186, "commentCount": 69, "commentText": "Hello from Dunes of Saudi Arabia🌍

Exploring the stunning dunes of Arabia was an adventure I’ll never forget! 🌵✨ We started off with an adrenaline-packed dune-bashing experience in a dune buggy, racing across the golden sands and feeling the thrill with every twist and turn. The endless expanse of dunes made it feel like we were in a scene from a movie—it was absolutely unreal!

After all the excitement, we took a moment to slow down and soak in the beauty of the desert. Watching the sunset over the dunes was pure magic. The sky turned into the most beautiful shades of orange, pink, and gold, lighting up the sand and creating a view that was straight out of a dream.

The combination of adventure and the peaceful beauty of the desert made this experience so special. It’s not just about the thrill of riding through the dunes but also about connecting with nature in such a unique and unforgettable way.

This was an unforgettable journey through the vibrant capital of Saudi Arabia with @visitsaudi 🇸🇦✨ My trip to Riyadh was a perfect blend of modern wonders and deep cultural heritage.

{"mediaType": 8, "likeCount": 27186, "commentCount": 69, "commentText": "Hello from Dunes of Saudi Arabia🌍

Exploring the stunning dunes of Arabia was an adventure I’ll never forget! 🌵✨ We started off with an adrenaline-packed dune-bashing experience in a dune buggy, racing across the golden sands and feeling the thrill with every twist and turn. The endless expanse of dunes made it feel like we were in a scene from a movie—it was absolutely unreal!

After all the excitement, we took a moment to slow down and soak in the beauty of the desert. Watching the sunset over the dunes was pure magic. The sky turned into the most beautiful shades of orange, pink, and gold, lighting up the sand and creating a view that was straight out of a dream.

The combination of adventure and the peaceful beauty of the desert made this experience so special. It’s not just about the thrill of riding through the dunes but also about connecting with nature in such a unique and unforgettable way.

If you’re ever in Saudi Arabia, exploring the Arabian desert and experiencing the magic of the dunes should definitely be on your list! 🇸🇦🌞
